<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870908-0150 </DOCNO><HL> Who's News:Apple Computer Inc.Revamps Sales Group</HL><DD> 09/08/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> AAPL WNEWSCOMPUTERS (EDP) </IN><DATELINE> CUPERTINO, Calif.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Apple Computer Inc. reorganized its domestic sales group into three geographic regions and named two new vice presidents.    Harold D. Copperman, 40-year-old former director of marketing for higher education at International Business Machines Corp.'s academic information systems unit, was named to the new post of vice president and general manager of Apple's sales operation in the Eastern U.S.    William B. Coldrick, 45, formerly director of all of Apple's domestic field sales, was named vice president and general manager of sales in the Western region. A spokeswoman for the computer maker said a vice president, Midwest operations, will be named in the near future.    As a result of the reorganization, the currently vacant position of vice president, U.S. sales, will be eliminated, the spokeswoman said. </TEXT></DOC>